IEBC clerks in some parts of Busia county have adopted a door-to-door approach in a bid to get voters to verify their biometric details with only three days left before the end of the exercise on Friday.There has been low turnout in some polling stations.An official who yesterday spoke on condition of anonymity said there has been low turnout at Lukonyi polling station in Burumba ward.&ldquo;We have resorted to using the house-to-house method as we try and unravel the mystery of why the polling station which recorded a huge turnout during the primaries is now lagging when it comes to verification,&rdquo; he said.